1
00:00:05,133 --> 00:00:06,766
ICHIGO (NARRATING):
I'm Ichigo Kurasaki.

2
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:08,866
And other than having the
ability to see spirits,

3
00:00:08,900 --> 00:00:11,100
I used to be an ordinary
high school student.

4
00:00:11,133 --> 00:00:12,566
But the day I met
Rukia Kuchiki, I

5
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:14,400
was given the powers
of a soul reaper

6
00:00:14,433 --> 00:00:16,366
in order to protect the
world of the living.

7
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,800
As I began my work as a
substitute soul reaper,

8
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:21,266
I found myself thrown into
a never ending battle.

9
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:24,033
In the midst of everything,
my best friend Orihime Inoue

10
00:00:24,066 --> 00:00:27,166
was abducted by ex soul
reaper captain Sosuke Aizen.

11
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,900
My friends Chad and
Udi you joined me

12
00:00:28,933 --> 00:00:30,733
as I raced to rescue Orihime.

13
00:00:30,766 --> 00:00:33,133
Once we arrived in Hueco
Mundo, we entered a fight

14
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:35,400
with powerful enemies
known as arrancars.

15
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:37,233
We were too late to
keep Aizen from entering

16
00:00:37,266 --> 00:00:40,033
the world of the living But
luckily, the 13 court guard

17
00:00:40,066 --> 00:00:41,966
squads were already
there to stop it.

18
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,233
An all out war was
about to begin!

19
00:00:45,266 --> 00:00:52,166
[theme music]

20
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,666
[foreign language]

21
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:30,146
NARRATOR: Soul
reapers and arrancars

22
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:32,980
faced off against each other
throughout Karakura Town.

23
00:02:33,013 --> 00:02:35,346
Rangiku Matsumoto
squared off against three

24
00:02:35,380 --> 00:02:40,180
of Harribel's proxiones,
Apacci, Mila Rose, and Sung-Sun.

25
00:02:40,213 --> 00:02:43,313
Rangiku noticed that her three
opponents did not get along

26
00:02:43,346 --> 00:02:44,946
and tried to use that
to her advantages

27
00:02:44,980 --> 00:02:46,446
as she confronted them.

28
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:48,913
But fighting three
against one took its toll,

29
00:02:48,946 --> 00:02:51,313
and gradually pushed
her into a corner.

30
00:02:51,346 --> 00:02:54,046
Then an unexpected
helper suddenly appeared.

31
00:02:57,213 --> 00:02:58,146
-[gasp]

32
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:02,946
Like I said, you
don't stand a chance!

33
00:03:09,713 --> 00:03:11,580
Nice try!

34
00:03:11,613 --> 00:03:13,546
You don't have what
it takes to handle me,

35
00:03:13,580 --> 00:03:15,046
let alone the three of us.

36
00:03:18,546 --> 00:03:22,446
[gasp]

37
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:22,946
-[grunt]

38
00:03:26,946 --> 00:03:29,913
What?

39
00:03:29,946 --> 00:03:30,580
It's you.

40
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:35,346
Momo.

41
00:03:38,646 --> 00:03:39,480
-Not bad.

42
00:03:39,513 --> 00:03:42,380
And she's a lieutenant, no less.

43
00:03:42,413 --> 00:03:44,446
Not that it matters, though.

44
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:47,013
An extra lieutenant doesn't
really change the equation.

45
00:03:51,413 --> 00:03:52,513
Sorry, cow.

46
00:03:52,546 --> 00:03:54,713
Time to die.

47
00:03:54,746 --> 00:03:55,180
-[gasp]

48
00:03:55,213 --> 00:03:55,713
-[gasp]

49
00:03:55,746 --> 00:03:57,646
-[gasp]

50
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:00,113
-What the-- what is this?

51
00:04:03,113 --> 00:04:03,913
-Now snap.

52
00:04:03,946 --> 00:04:04,813
Tobiume!

53
00:04:04,846 --> 00:04:07,280
-[grunting]

54
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:15,880
-[panting]

55
00:04:15,913 --> 00:04:18,780
-Are you sure you're
all right, Momo?

56
00:04:18,813 --> 00:04:20,046
-Yes.

57
00:04:20,080 --> 00:04:21,580
Sorry about that.

58
00:04:21,613 --> 00:04:23,946
I had never used that
combination of techniques

59
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:24,780
before.

60
00:04:24,813 --> 00:04:25,780
RANGIKU (VOICEOVER): Incredible.

61
00:04:25,813 --> 00:04:27,546
Having the ability
to combine several

62
00:04:27,580 --> 00:04:30,946
of these kido in her
own unique fashion?

63
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:31,846
[gasp]

64
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:34,080
-Thrust, Cierva!

65
00:04:34,113 --> 00:04:36,346
-Eat your fill, Liona!

66
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:38,146
-Strangled to death, Anaconda!

67
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,413
-[grunt]

68
00:04:43,446 --> 00:04:44,880
-It can't be!

69
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:53,980
-[battle cry]

70
00:04:54,013 --> 00:05:05,313
[grunting]

71
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:06,780
Take that and that and that!

72
00:05:06,813 --> 00:05:09,780
[grunting] That!

73
00:05:09,813 --> 00:05:11,980
-What's bothering you?

74
00:05:12,013 --> 00:05:13,480
-Your partner over there.

75
00:05:13,513 --> 00:05:16,413
Lilinette is the
name she goes by?

76
00:05:16,446 --> 00:05:17,946
She's pretty wild.

77
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:21,346
You all right with that?

78
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:23,746
-[grunting]

79
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:25,380
-She's not very effective.

80
00:05:25,413 --> 00:05:27,413
Why don't you say
something to her?

81
00:05:27,446 --> 00:05:29,846
-[sigh]

82
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,080
I gave up trying.

83
00:05:31,113 --> 00:05:32,880
She never listens to me.

84
00:05:32,913 --> 00:05:34,013
But so what?

85
00:05:34,046 --> 00:05:35,780
Why do you care?

86
00:05:35,813 --> 00:05:37,846
I would expect you to
be concentrating more

87
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,446
on your own situation.

88
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:42,280
-How polite of you.

89
00:05:42,313 --> 00:05:43,746
You wouldn't want
me to lose focus.

90
00:05:47,913 --> 00:05:54,780
-[battle cry]

91
00:05:54,813 --> 00:05:56,146
-Bakudo number eight.

92
00:05:56,180 --> 00:05:57,413
Seki.

93
00:05:57,446 --> 00:05:59,813
-[battle cry]

94
00:05:59,846 --> 00:06:00,780
[groan]

95
00:06:00,813 --> 00:06:04,680
[grunting]

96
00:06:18,413 --> 00:06:21,046
No way.

97
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:23,113
-I've been in many
battles, and I've

98
00:06:23,146 --> 00:06:26,113
seen hundreds of
different ceros.

99
00:06:26,146 --> 00:06:28,413
So I'm going to
tell you the truth.

100
00:06:28,446 --> 00:06:29,880
Your cero is immature.

101
00:06:29,913 --> 00:06:32,513
It's not even at
the level of Menos.

102
00:06:32,546 --> 00:06:35,146
As you just observed,
I can knock it down

103
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:37,380
with my bare hands.

104
00:06:37,413 --> 00:06:39,413
You are completely unmatched.

105
00:06:39,446 --> 00:06:41,580
You should stop and go home.

106
00:06:41,613 --> 00:06:43,846
I'll give you one
chance to withdraw.

107
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,446
If you continue, you're
facing certain death.

108
00:06:58,546 --> 00:07:00,313
-I didn't think
my attack would be

109
00:07:00,346 --> 00:07:02,480
enough to outright defeat them.

110
00:07:02,513 --> 00:07:04,746
But they're virtually unscathed.

111
00:07:04,780 --> 00:07:07,613
-Their injuries heal when
they take resurrection form.

112
00:07:07,646 --> 00:07:10,846
That's how they've all
managed to make it this far.

113
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:12,313
-[grunt]

114
00:07:12,346 --> 00:07:15,246
Sorry I haven't been
more help to you.

115
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:16,246
-Mila Rose.

116
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:17,113
Sung-Sun.

117
00:07:17,146 --> 00:07:18,246
Let's get this over with.

118
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:19,846
It's time to end
this silly battle

119
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:21,646
and get back to Master Harribel.

120
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:24,513
-I don't know why you're getting
so worked up over these two.

121
00:07:24,546 --> 00:07:27,546
We're going to need
to step up our game.

122
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:29,513
-No other choice, really.

123
00:07:29,546 --> 00:07:32,380
-Man, I can't
fricking believe this.

124
00:07:32,413 --> 00:07:37,046
We're really going to waste
it on this pair of losers?

125
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:41,846
-[grunt]

126
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:42,846
-Quimera Parca.

127
00:07:50,713 --> 00:07:51,646
-[gasp]

128
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:52,613
What the?

129
00:07:56,513 --> 00:07:58,280
What in the world is that?

130
00:08:01,713 --> 00:08:07,246
-[gasp]

131
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:28,146
-Quimera Parca.

132
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:30,346
It's our pet, created
when the three of us

133
00:08:30,380 --> 00:08:32,213
combine our left arms together.

134
00:08:32,246 --> 00:08:35,813
You have to admit,
he's a work of art.

135
00:08:35,846 --> 00:08:37,113
We like to call him Ayon.

136
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:43,480
-[gasp]

137
00:08:43,513 --> 00:08:44,980
-[gasp]

138
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:52,080
RANGIKU (NARRATING): Why do I
feel so cold all of a sudden?

139
00:08:52,113 --> 00:08:54,813
It's like I'm peering
into a deep pit,

140
00:08:54,846 --> 00:08:59,913
and the bottom is so far
away I can't even see it.

141
00:08:59,946 --> 00:09:08,580
-[grunting]

142
00:09:08,613 --> 00:09:10,413
-Just the kind of
strength I'd expect

143
00:09:10,446 --> 00:09:13,080
from someone who's achieved
the rank of captain.

144
00:09:13,113 --> 00:09:17,380
-If you continue to waste time
talking, you will be destroyed.

145
00:09:20,346 --> 00:09:21,813
You won't escape next time.

146
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:34,146
-[grunt]

147
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:36,846
-[moaning]

148
00:09:41,380 --> 00:09:42,346
-[gasp]

149
00:09:49,846 --> 00:09:50,813
-[gasp]

150
00:09:50,846 --> 00:09:52,313
Haineko!

151
00:09:52,346 --> 00:09:53,313
[cry]

152
00:09:57,346 --> 00:09:59,313
[moaning]

153
00:10:04,846 --> 00:10:08,313
-Oh, did I forget to warn you?

154
00:10:08,346 --> 00:10:10,513
Ayon is deadly, so
you have to be careful

155
00:10:10,546 --> 00:10:12,246
when you're around him.

156
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:16,246
-[moaning]

157
00:10:22,713 --> 00:10:24,180
-[cry]

158
00:10:24,213 --> 00:10:24,680
Rangiku!

159
00:10:28,180 --> 00:10:28,646
-[gasp]

160
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:35,613
[grunting]

161
00:10:35,646 --> 00:10:36,113
Rangiku.

162
00:10:43,113 --> 00:10:43,580
-Rangiku!

163
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:51,513
Rangiku!

164
00:10:55,046 --> 00:10:57,513
Bakudo number 37, Tsuriboshi!

165
00:11:07,013 --> 00:11:07,980
-[gasp]

166
00:11:08,013 --> 00:11:09,446
-Don't worry, Rangiku.

167
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:11,446
I'm going to heal your injuries!

168
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,946
MOMO (NARRATING):
He really got her.

169
00:11:12,980 --> 00:11:15,513
He smashed her from just
bellow the ribs down

170
00:11:15,546 --> 00:11:18,480
through the intestinal area.

171
00:11:18,513 --> 00:11:20,880
She can't breathe
with these injuries.

172
00:11:20,913 --> 00:11:24,346
I have to hurry!

173
00:11:24,380 --> 00:11:26,346
[gasp]

174
00:11:26,380 --> 00:11:31,846
[moaning]

175
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:34,313
[gasp]

176
00:11:34,346 --> 00:11:38,813
[moaning]

177
00:11:38,846 --> 00:11:42,813
There are broken bones
throughout my body.

178
00:11:42,846 --> 00:11:44,813
Both Rungiku and myself
have been taken out

179
00:11:44,846 --> 00:11:46,813
within moments of each other.

180
00:11:46,846 --> 00:11:48,313
This is crazy.

181
00:11:48,346 --> 00:11:52,580
There is no way we can
win against this thing.

182
00:11:52,613 --> 00:11:54,713
-Bakudo number 37, Tsuriboshi!

183
00:12:14,246 --> 00:12:16,213
-[gasp]

184
00:12:16,246 --> 00:12:19,146
Izuru.

185
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:22,146
Shuhei.

186
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:25,380
-You did an extremely effective
job holding him off, Momo.

187
00:12:25,413 --> 00:12:28,346
Rest a while.

188
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:30,546
Izuru.

189
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:32,346
Let's get rid of this monster.

190
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:49,773
-What the?

191
00:12:49,806 --> 00:12:51,206
Who are these bozos?

192
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:53,440
SPEAKER (OFFSCREEN):
They must be her friends.

193
00:12:53,473 --> 00:12:56,906
I saw them coming from the
direction of the pillars.

194
00:12:56,940 --> 00:13:00,673
-So if you saw them coming, why
didn't you try and stop them?

195
00:13:00,706 --> 00:13:02,773
I thought you were in
a much better position

196
00:13:02,806 --> 00:13:04,106
to see their approach.

197
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:07,806
Or are your eyes just useless
holes sitting on your face?

198
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,040
-What's that?

199
00:13:09,073 --> 00:13:10,340
-Stop it, both of you.

200
00:13:10,373 --> 00:13:12,173
We're right in the
middle of a battle.

201
00:13:12,206 --> 00:13:13,773
Concentrate!

202
00:13:13,806 --> 00:13:15,740
-Hmph.

203
00:13:15,773 --> 00:13:18,940
-[grunt]

204
00:13:18,973 --> 00:13:20,806
-They must be here to
help their friends.

205
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,906
What is it with these guys?

206
00:13:25,940 --> 00:13:28,706
They love to interfere in
other people's battles.

207
00:13:28,740 --> 00:13:29,806
Ayon!

208
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:31,640
Don't give them the
opportunity to butt in.

209
00:13:31,673 --> 00:13:35,006
Kill them both now!

210
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,973
Ayon!

211
00:13:37,006 --> 00:13:39,873
[groan]

212
00:13:39,906 --> 00:13:42,140
Looks to me like he's
trying to ignore us.

213
00:13:42,173 --> 00:13:43,673
-Don't be stupid.

214
00:13:43,706 --> 00:13:45,073
Look at him.

215
00:13:45,106 --> 00:13:47,573
What makes you think he has the
capacity to hear a word we say?

216
00:13:47,606 --> 00:13:50,873
-Well, he's got to have eardrums
on him somewhere, doesn't he?

217
00:13:50,906 --> 00:13:53,273
-I'm not absolutely sure.

218
00:13:53,306 --> 00:13:55,940
I've never seen him react
when we speak to him.

219
00:13:55,973 --> 00:13:58,140
Maybe he just reads our minds.

220
00:13:58,173 --> 00:13:59,906
But apart from
that, would you mind

221
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:02,540
not asking me to agree with
you when we're having to fight?

222
00:14:02,573 --> 00:14:04,006
It's very annoying.

223
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:05,373
-Really?

224
00:14:05,406 --> 00:14:08,440
I have to presume that Ayon
gets his nasty side from you.

225
00:14:08,473 --> 00:14:11,173
-That may be so, but he
gets his face from you.

226
00:14:11,206 --> 00:14:13,740
Those ugly horns are
exactly like yours.

227
00:14:13,773 --> 00:14:16,840
-Don't force me to kill you
before I kill those soul

228
00:14:16,873 --> 00:14:17,606
reapers.

229
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,173
-This fighting stops now!

230
00:14:19,206 --> 00:14:21,473
It doesn't matter
who Ayon takes after.

231
00:14:21,506 --> 00:14:24,006
-That's because he gets
his temperament from you.

232
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:26,206
I'm sure he's doomed to
be alone and unmarried

233
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,573
because no one can stand him.

234
00:14:27,606 --> 00:14:28,573
-Get bent, lady!

235
00:14:28,606 --> 00:14:29,406
[interposing voices]

236
00:14:33,973 --> 00:14:36,773
-What are those women
screaming about up there?

237
00:14:36,806 --> 00:14:38,173
They've lost it.

238
00:14:38,206 --> 00:14:39,040
-Yeah.

239
00:14:39,073 --> 00:14:41,740
Don't worry about them, Izuru.

240
00:14:41,773 --> 00:14:42,306
-You're right.

241
00:14:45,973 --> 00:14:47,006
-Know what?

242
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:49,006
I'm going to kill
both of you, some day!

243
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:50,706
-If you've got the
game, bring it all!

244
00:14:50,740 --> 00:14:51,206
-Mmm-hmm.

245
00:14:54,706 --> 00:14:57,606
-I knew it was a bad
idea to bring him out.

246
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:58,740
He's nearly uncontrollable.

247
00:15:04,806 --> 00:15:06,606
-Izuru.

248
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:08,706
I'll handle this guy.

249
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:11,273
You can go take care
of Momo and Rangiku.

250
00:15:11,306 --> 00:15:14,540
-[groan]

251
00:15:14,573 --> 00:15:15,573
Wait a minute.

252
00:15:15,606 --> 00:15:16,973
You sure you want
to fight him alone?

253
00:15:17,006 --> 00:15:19,006
-Who said anything
about fighting alone?

254
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:20,706
After you've done
emergency first aid,

255
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:23,940
hide them both using Kido,
then come back here to help!

256
00:15:23,973 --> 00:15:27,306
-Rangiku needs assistance
quickly or she might die.

257
00:15:27,340 --> 00:15:30,773
Don't forget, you're a
former member of squad four.

258
00:15:30,806 --> 00:15:34,640
-I'm afraid that
was a long time ago.

259
00:15:34,673 --> 00:15:35,806
-I'm counting on you.

260
00:15:38,373 --> 00:15:38,940
-All right.

261
00:15:38,973 --> 00:15:39,840
Let's do it.

262
00:15:47,106 --> 00:15:48,073
-What the hell?

263
00:15:48,106 --> 00:15:50,373
Why are you just
standing there, Ayon?

264
00:15:50,406 --> 00:15:53,840
They just grabbed that big cow!

265
00:15:53,873 --> 00:15:55,006
-Bakudo number 73.

266
00:16:03,506 --> 00:16:03,973
Tozansho!

267
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:11,106
I'll heal your injuries
as soon as as I can.

268
00:16:11,140 --> 00:16:12,740
Just hang in there, Momo!

269
00:16:12,773 --> 00:16:15,773
-Don't worry, I'm all right.

270
00:16:15,806 --> 00:16:17,673
It's Rangiku.

271
00:16:17,706 --> 00:16:19,606
Hurry up and help her!

272
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:22,506
[gasp]

273
00:16:22,540 --> 00:16:26,440
IZURU (NARRATING): Momo's
in pretty bad shape herself.

274
00:16:26,473 --> 00:16:29,606
She's either got a broken rib
or even worse-- one of her lungs

275
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:30,140
is collapsed.

276
00:16:33,473 --> 00:16:41,773
However, Rangiku's condition
is even more critical.

277
00:16:41,806 --> 00:16:43,140
Here goes.

278
00:16:43,173 --> 00:16:45,473
I hope my healing
skills are still sharp.

279
00:16:56,606 --> 00:17:00,473
SHUHEI (NARRATING): This
thing is a complete unknown.

280
00:17:00,506 --> 00:17:03,973
I'd better try and
evaluate its capabilities.

281
00:17:04,006 --> 00:17:07,873
Hado number 11, Tsuzuri Raiden!

282
00:17:11,373 --> 00:17:12,840
Didn't have an effect.

283
00:17:23,740 --> 00:17:25,173
[grunt]

284
00:17:28,706 --> 00:17:33,773
-Well, now That was
a pretty good move.

285
00:17:33,806 --> 00:17:38,340
-This one's stronger than
either of those two cows.

286
00:17:38,373 --> 00:17:39,740
-Ha.

287
00:17:39,773 --> 00:17:42,673
In my opinion, they're all the
same, judging by that attack.

288
00:17:54,373 --> 00:17:56,040
SHUHEI (NARRATING):
It was effective.

289
00:17:56,073 --> 00:17:57,606
I can beat him!

290
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:59,606
This thing's weakness is Kido!

291
00:18:06,573 --> 00:18:09,540
[scream]

292
00:18:09,573 --> 00:18:10,040
[gasp]

293
00:18:15,406 --> 00:18:15,873
-Surprise!

294
00:18:27,373 --> 00:18:27,973
-Damn monster.

295
00:18:33,573 --> 00:18:36,606
He had no trouble breaking free.

296
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,973
He's a lot more powerful
than I suspected.

297
00:18:44,706 --> 00:18:45,640
Damn it!

298
00:18:45,673 --> 00:18:47,373
-Shuhei!

299
00:18:47,406 --> 00:18:50,606
-[grunting]

300
00:18:56,306 --> 00:19:00,440
IZURU (NARRATING): I've got
to finish healing Rangiku.

301
00:19:00,473 --> 00:19:01,906
-[grunting]

302
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:04,506
Let go of me!

303
00:19:04,540 --> 00:19:11,973
[grunting]

304
00:19:16,973 --> 00:19:17,940
[gasp]

305
00:19:22,940 --> 00:19:24,406
[moaning]

306
00:19:26,973 --> 00:19:28,840
TETSUZAEMON (NARRATING):
It hasn't noticed me

307
00:19:28,873 --> 00:19:30,773
yet I think I've got it.

308
00:19:35,073 --> 00:19:35,540
[gasp]

309
00:19:40,473 --> 00:19:41,906
[scream]

310
00:19:47,273 --> 00:19:47,806
-Tetsuzaemon!

311
00:19:52,906 --> 00:20:07,773
[moaning]

312
00:20:07,806 --> 00:20:09,406
-I guess this fight's over.

313
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:10,773
That was fast.

314
00:20:10,806 --> 00:20:13,973
-I thought they'd be able to
generate a much better effort.

315
00:20:14,006 --> 00:20:16,173
How disappointing.

316
00:20:16,206 --> 00:20:19,373
APACCI (OFFSCREEN): Ayon
was too strong for them,

317
00:20:19,406 --> 00:20:20,806
and they were too cocky.

318
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:23,640
It serves them right.

319
00:20:23,673 --> 00:20:26,673
Ayon, hurry up so you can
finish off the rest of them!

320
00:20:29,573 --> 00:20:33,506
-[MOANING

